<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Redis Session Check</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 50px auto;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .redis-data {
            background-color: #f8f9fa;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            margin: 15px 0;
        }

        pre {
            background-color: #282c34;
            color: #abb2bf;
            padding: 15px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            overflow-x: auto;
        }

        h3 {
            color: #dc3545;
        }

        a {
            display: inline-block;
            margin-top: 20px;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            background-color: #007bff;
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }

            a:hover {
                background-color: #0056b3;
            }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>🔴 Redis Session Data Inspector</h2>

    <div class="redis-data">
        <h3>Session ID (Redis Key):</h3>
        <pre>@ViewBag.SessionId</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="redis-data">
        <h3>User Session Object (JSON in Redis):</h3>
        <pre>@ViewBag.SessionJson</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="redis-data">
        <h3>Individual Session Values:</h3>
        <p><strong>User ID:</strong> @ViewBag.UserId</p>
        <p><strong>Username:</strong> @ViewBag.UserName</p>
    </div>

    <div class="redis-data">
        <h3>How It Works:</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>When you login, user data is serialized to JSON and stored in Redis</li>
            <li>Redis key format: "SessionDemo_" + SessionId</li>
            <li>On each request, ASP.NET Core retrieves session data from Redis</li>
            <li>Session expires after 30 minutes of inactivity (configurable)</li>
            <li>Redis stores this in memory for ultra-fast access</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <a href="/Account/Dashboard">← Back to Dashboard</a>
</body>
</html>